  "text": "Imidazolium D-camphorsulfonate (D-ImCS) is a metal-free organic molecular ionic crystal: an imidazolium cation paired with a homochiral D-camphorsulfonate anion, linked by N\u2013H\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7O hydrogen-bonded chains. It crystallizes in the chiral-polar monoclinic space group P2\u2081 (point group 2) at 173 K and is a molecular ferroelectric, undergoing a 222F2-type ferroelectric phase transition at Tc = 370 K. Ferroelectricity is confirmed by PFM domain switching and hysteresis loops; the quasi-static (Berlincourt) piezoelectric coefficient along the polar [010] axis is \u00b120 pC/N, comparable to triglycine sulfate.",

